<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FF6A8A65FE0D1E28" box="[136,446,861,888]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachycephalus">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FF6A8A65FE0D1E28" bold="true" box="[136,446,861,888]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Melocactus pachycephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="700CC0085953FFF3FF6A8ABCFEF81923" blockId="0.[136,1452,861,1139]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
In a recent nomenclatural work concerning the Brazilian cacti belonging to the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FBF88ABCFE8B1EEF" authority="Salm-Dyck (Taylor &amp; Zappi 2020: 256 - 258)" authorityName="Salm-Dyck (Taylor &amp; Zappi" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cereeae">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FBF88ABCFBC11ECB" box="[1050,1138,900,923]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Cereeae</emphasis>
Salm-Dyck (
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FAE08ABBFE821EEF" author="Taylor, N. P. &amp; Zappi, D. C." pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="256 - 258" refId="ref1800" refString="Taylor, N. P. &amp; Zappi, D. C. (2020) Nomenclatural adjustments in Brazilian Cereeae (Cactaceae). Phytotaxa 470 (3): 256 - 258. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 470.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">Taylor &amp; Zappi 2020: 256–258</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FEA58A9FFCBC1EEF" box="[327,783,935,959]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FEA58A9FFD0E1EEF" box="[327,701,935,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pachycephalus" subSpecies="nomen">Melocactus pachycephalus nomen</taxonomicName>
novum
</emphasis>
, based on 
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FC6F8A90FDB71EB3" authority="N. P. Taylor (1991: 40)" authorityName="N. P. Taylor" authorityPageNumber="40" authorityYear="1991" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pachyacanthus" subSpecies="viridis">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FC6F8A90FBE71EEF" box="[909,1108,935,959]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">M. pachyacanthus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FBBD8A9FFA1F1EEF" author="Buining, A. F. &amp; Brederoo, A. J." box="[1119,1452,935,959]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref1464" refString="Buining, A. F. &amp; Brederoo, A. J. (1975) Melocactus pachyacanthus spec. nova. Kakteen Und Andere Sukkulenten 27 (1): 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1975">Buining &amp; Brederoo (1975: 1)</bibRefCitation>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FF308AF3FEA51EB3" box="[210,278,971,995]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">viridis</emphasis>
N.P. 
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FEA78AF3FDB71EB3" author="Taylor, N. P." box="[325,516,971,995]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref1680" refString="Taylor, N. P. (1991) The genus Melocactus in Central and South America. Bradleya 9: 1 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.25223 / brad. n 9.1991. a 1" type="journal article" year="1991">Taylor (1991: 40)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed at specific level to replace the illegitimate 
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FB858AF4FF121957" authority="Guiggi (2020 a: 3)" authorityName="Guiggi" authorityPageNumber="3" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridescens">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FB858AF4FAB01EB3" box="[1127,1283,971,995]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">M. viridescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FAEB8AF3FF121957" author="Guiggi, A." pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="2 - 4" refId="ref1499" refString="Guiggi, A. (2020 a) Brazil: Nomenclatural Revision in Cactaceae. Cactology V, Supplement 8: 2 - 4. https: // doi. org / 10.2985 / 026.025.0102" type="journal article" year="2020">Guiggi (2020a: 3)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter name is, in fact, a later homonym (and illegitimate according to the Art. 53.1 of ICN; see 
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FB5C8AD7FA3B1957" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1214,1416,1007,1031]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="ref1908" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FAF58AC8FAFF1957" box="[1303,1356,1007,1031]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FF6A8D2CFC68197B" authority="(Torrey &amp; Gray 1840: 554) Nuttall ex Teschemacher (1845: 293)" authorityName="Nuttall ex Teschemacher" authorityPageNumber="293" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Torrey &amp; Gray" baseAuthorityPageNumber="554" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[136,987,1043,1067]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridescens">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FF6A8D2CFE90197B" box="[136,291,1043,1067]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">M. viridescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FED28D2BFDF2197B" author="Torrey, J. &amp; Gray, A." box="[304,577,1043,1067]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" refId="ref1873" refString="Torrey, J. &amp; Gray, A. (1840) A flora of North America, vol. 1 (4). Wiley &amp; Putnam, New York, 711 pp." type="book" year="1840">Torrey &amp; Gray 1840: 554</bibRefCitation>
) Nuttall ex 
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FD5F8D2BFC68197B" author="Teschemacher, J. E." box="[701,987,1043,1067]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="293 - 294" refId="ref1847" refString="Teschemacher, J. E. (1845) Note on Melocactus viridescens Nutt. Boston Journal of Natural History 5: 293 - 294." type="journal article" year="1845">Teschemacher (1845: 293)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, 
<bibRefCitation id="1422BDF95953FFF3FB998D2BFA89197B" author="Guiggi, A." box="[1147,1338,1043,1067]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="2" refId="ref1534" refString="Guiggi, A. (2020 b) Brazil: Nomenclatural Revision in Cactaceae II. Cactology V, Supplement 10: 2. https: // doi. org / 10.2985 / 026.025.0102" type="journal article" year="2020">Guiggi (2020b: 2)</bibRefCitation>
have been noticed his nomenclatural error and already proposed a new name, i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FC958D0FFB25191F" authorityName="Guiggi" authorityYear="2020" box="[887,1174,1079,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neoviridescens">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FC958D0FFB25191F" box="[887,1174,1079,1103]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Melocactus neoviridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The complete taxonomic treatment follows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
