<subSubSection id="38A993835953FFF3FF5F8CFBFBD31BAB" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="700CC0085953FFF3FF5F8CFBFD1E18AF" blockId="0.[136,1451,1475,1787]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FF5F8CFBFEF2188B" bold="true" box="[189,321,1475,1499]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Etymology:</emphasis>
―From Greek ‘neos’ new (to avoid a homonym) and Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="B7B3BB8B5953FFF3FC258CFBFB8C188B" authorityName="Nuttall ex Teschemacher" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Torrey &amp; Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[967,1087,1475,1499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Melocactus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridescens">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FC258CFBFB8C188B" box="[967,1087,1475,1499]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">viridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ to be green referred to the colour of the epidermis (Eggli &amp; Newton 2004: 164, 253).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="700CC0085953FFF3FF5F8F33FCCA1B3B" blockId="0.[136,1451,1475,1787]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="42C71C1A5953FFF3FF5F8F33FC921B73" bold="true" box="[189,801,1547,1571]" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
